# EmailJS — contact form delivery (https://www.emailjs.com/)
# Sign up for a free EmailJS account, then:
#   1. Add an Email Service that authenticates the sender admin@dubcall.com
#      (e.g. Gmail/SMTP/Custom). EmailJS will use that mailbox as the "From".
#   2. Create two email templates and paste their IDs below:
#        - VITE_EMAILJS_BUSINESS_TEMPLATE → sends to {{to_email}} = business@dubcall.com
#        - VITE_EMAILJS_CUSTOMER_TEMPLATE → sends to {{to_email}} = the customer
#   3. Copy your public key from Account → API Keys.
# Variables exposed to the templates: name, email, company, topic, urgency,
# message, console_url, business_email, submitted_at, to_email, to_name, reply_to.

VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=
VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=
VITE_EMAILJS_BUSINESS_TEMPLATE=
VITE_EMAILJS_CUSTOMER_TEMPLATE=
